data.enText: a soft wet substance that is made especially by crushing sth
Cook the fruit gently until it forms a pulp.
His face had been beaten to a pulp (= very badly beaten) .
a soft substance that is made by crushing wood, cloth or other material and then used to make paper
the soft part inside some fruit and vegetables

data.chText: 把水果慢慢地煮成软糊状。
data.enText: Cook the fruit slowly until soft and pulpy.
to crush or beat sth so that it becomes soft and wet

data.chText: 没卖出去的小说只好化成纸浆。
data.enText: Unsold copies of the novel had to be pulped.

data.chText: 粗制滥造的；庸俗刺激的
data.enText: badly written and often intended to shock people

tr: the soft inner part of a tooth
an inexpensive magazine printed on poor quality paper

example: he pounded it to a pulp

tr: a soft moist part of a fruit
remove the pulp from, as from a fruit

value.def: If an object is pressed into a pulp, it is crushed or beaten until it is soft, smooth, and wet.

example.ex: The olives are crushed to a pulp by stone rollers.

value.def: In fruit or vegetables, the pulp is the soft part inside the skin.

example.ex: Make maximum use of the whole fruit, including the pulp which is high in fibre.
example.tran: 水果的各个部分都要最大限度地利用，包括富含纤维的果肉。

value.def: Wood pulp is material made from crushed wood. It is used to make paper.
People refer to stories or novels as pulp fiction when they consider them to be of poor quality and intentionally shocking or sensational.
value.tran: （故事或小说）粗制滥造的，庸俗刺激的，耸人听闻的

value.def: If paper, vegetables, or fruit are pulped, they are crushed into a smooth, wet paste.

example.ex: Onions can be boiled and pulped to a puree.
example.tran: 洋葱可以煮一下打成糊。
奶油状或浆状的西红柿

value.tran: 把（纸张、蔬菜或水果）打成浆

value.def: If money or documents are pulped, they are destroyed. This is done to stop the money being used or to stop the documents being seen by the public.

example.ex: 25 million pounds worth of five pound notes have been pulped because the designers made a mistake.
example.tran: 因为设计者们犯了一个错误，致使价值2,500万英镑的5英镑纸钞被化成纸浆。

value.def: If someone is beaten to a pulp or beaten to pulp, they are hit repeatedly until they are very badly injured.

example.ex: I tried to talk myself out of a fight and got beaten to a pulp instead by three other boys.
example.tran: 我尽量克制住自己不要打架，却被另外3个男孩打成了重伤。

value.tran: 把…打得稀巴烂；把…打成重伤
